==English==
===Etymology===
alteration of ''sabi'' know (in English-based creoles and pidgins), from Portuguese ''sabe'' he knows, from ''saber'' to know, from Latin ''sapere'' to be wise

===Adjective===
#(''informal'') [[shrewd]], well-informed and [[perceptive]].

